<div class=3D"u-rte-resources u-fw-500">

<p>Oh boy. <em>Integrals</em>. <a href=3D"https://photomath.com/articles/wh=
at-is-calculus-definition-applications-and-concepts/">Calculus</a> wasn=E2=
=80=99t complicated enough=E2=80=A6 now we have these big swirly lines, too=
?!</p>
<p>If that=E2=80=99s what=E2=80=99s running through your head right now, yo=
u can stop those thoughts in their tracks. Integral calculus actually isn=
=E2=80=99t as intimidating as it seems!</p>
<p>Once we really get into it, you might even think integrals are =E2=80=94=
 dare we say =E2=80=94 <em>cool</em>?</p>
<p>There=E2=80=99s only one way to find out! Let=E2=80=99s get started.</p>
<h2>What is an integral?</h2>
<p>Depending on where you are in your learning journey, an integral can rep=
resent the answer to a few different questions. At their core in <a href=3D=
"https://photomath.com/articles/what-is-calculus-definition-applications-an=
d-concepts/">calculus</a>, integration helps you find the anti-derivative o=
f a function; in other words, finding an integral is the inverse of finding=
 a <a href=3D"https://photomath.com/articles/what-is-a-derivative-derivativ=
es-definition-and-meaning/">derivative</a>.</p>
<p>As you work through your calculus lessons, you=E2=80=99ll see that there=
 are different types of integrals, including:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://photomath.com/articles/indefinite-integrals/">Indefi=
nite integrals</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://photomath.com/articles/definite-integrals/">Definite=
 integrals</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://photomath.com/articles/improper-integrals/">Improper=
 integrals</a></li>
</ul>
<p>The process of finding an integral is called =E2=80=9Cintegration,=E2=80=
=9D so an integral can also be thought of as the product of integration. Th=
ere are several ways to evaluate integrals, such as the substitution method=
 or partial integration.</p>
<p>Because integration is the inverse of differentiation, integrals are eas=
ier to understand when your knowledge of derivatives is already solid. If y=
ou still need a little help putting the pieces together, we can help you wi=
th <a href=3D"https://photomath.com/articles/what-is-a-derivative-derivativ=
es-definition-and-meaning/">derivatives</a> first!</p>
<h3>Definition of an integral</h3>
<p>As we mentioned, there are a few different types of integrals. That mean=
s we=E2=80=99ll have a few different definitions, as well.</p>
<p>Here are the integral definitions that you=E2=80=99ll likely need (and u=
se!) the most:</p>
